1. A method of separating toe nails while applying polish material to the toe nails comprising of the steps of:
a) providing a soft pliable puffy round tubular shape ranging from ½ inches to 1 and ½ inches having a variety of different colors and being made of corn starch material; the toe separator being molded and formed of biodegradable material and will dissolve under running water,
b) gently pinching each of the toe separators along the center as you place them between the toes for comfort and applying nail polish material onto the nails;
